    "feature_text_Vj93Ta": {
      "type": "feature-text",
      "settings": {
        "richtext": "<p>LEATHER GOODS PURCHASE POLICY AND COMMITMENT TO CRAFT<br/><br/>Last update: 15 April 2026<br/><br/>At PEGGY HARTANTO, we are deeply moved by the resonance our collections have found within our community. We acknowledge the frustration that arises when a desired piece is no longer available. However, our commitment to excellence is an intentional journey, and we see it as our responsibility to maintain the quality and integrity of our production over the pursuit of scale.<br/><br/>We are constantly improving our production system and capacity, and our production schedule is currently secured for months to come. Because our leather goods involve precise cutting, meticulous hand-finishing, and complex construction, we cannot accelerate our pace without compromising the craftsmanship of the design.<br/><br/>To ensure that our pieces reach our community in a transparent manner, we have implemented the following measures: <br/><br/>Acquisitions are limited to <strong>one (1) piece per SKU, per individual, per day.</strong> <br/>To respect your time and provide an equitable experience for all, we have recently transitioned our boutique waiting lists to our <strong>Online Store.</strong> This ensures that every client, regardless of their location, has an equal opportunity to acquire our pieces as they become available.<br/><br/>We monitor our distribution methods daily and listen closely to the feedback from our community across all channels to ensure our system remains as seamless as our silhouettes.<br/><br/>We understand that waiting requires patience, and we thank you for valuing the hand-made nature of our work. We hope you will cherish your PEGGY HARTANTO pieces for a long time.<br/><br/>For further inquiries regarding availability or our process, please contact us at <strong>lydia@peggyhartanto.com</strong>.<br/><br/></p>",
